      "display_name": "Browser Cookies",
      "description_for_humans": "Import browser cookies for authenticated testing — lets the agent browse pages that require login",
      "description_for_agent": "Import cookies from a user-provided cookie export or from a login flow. Steps: 1) Ask the user for cookies (they can export from Chrome DevTools > Application > Cookies, or use a browser extension). 2) Load cookies into the Browser Tool session. 3) Verify authentication by visiting a protected page and confirming access. 4) Store cookie config in .slack-context/_browser-cookies.json (encrypted/redacted — never store raw session tokens in git). This enables QA, Canary Monitor, and Browse skills to test authenticated pages and admin panels.",
