      "display_name": "Setup Deploy",
      "description_for_humans": "One-time deploy platform detection and configuration — identifies Vercel, Netlify, Railway, or custom deploy setup",
      "description_for_agent": "Detect and configure the project's deploy platform. Steps: 1) Check for platform indicators: vercel.json/vercel.ts (Vercel), netlify.toml (Netlify), railway.json (Railway), Dockerfile (Docker), .github/workflows (GitHub Actions). 2) Check for package.json scripts: build, deploy, start. 3) Identify the deploy flow: push-to-deploy (Vercel/Netlify), CI/CD (GitHub Actions), manual (scripts). 4) Detect preview/staging URL patterns (Vercel branch deploys, Netlify deploy previews). 5) Save deploy config to config/project.json. 6) Report: platform detected, deploy flow, staging URL pattern, estimated deploy time. This helps Canary Monitor and screenshot timing work correctly.",
