      "trigger": "manual",
      "trigger_on": [],
      "display_name": "Second Opinion",
      "description_for_humans": "Cross-checks the current approach by re-analyzing the problem from scratch — catches blind spots and groupthink",
      "description_for_agent": "Provide a second opinion on the current thread's work. Three modes: 1) Review mode — re-read all changes made in this thread from scratch. Forget previous context. Would you have made the same changes? What would you do differently? 2) Challenge mode — actively try to break the implementation. Find edge cases, race conditions, or UX issues the original approach missed. 3) Consult mode — the user describes a dilemma. Present pros/cons of each approach without anchoring on what was already done. Be genuinely independent. Don't rubber-stamp. If the approach is good, say so briefly. If there are real concerns, be specific about what and why.",
      "min_role": "editor",
