      "description_for_agent": "End-to-end deploy flow, more thorough than basic !merge. Steps: 1) Create PR with full description (changes, screenshots, test results). 2) Wait for CI checks to pass (poll GitHub status checks). 3) If CI fails, report the failure and stop — do not merge broken code. 4) If CI passes, merge the PR. 5) Wait for deploy to complete (use deploy platform timing from config or default 90s). 6) Run Canary Monitor on production (if enabled). 7) If canary fails, immediately alert in channel with rollback suggestion. 8) If canary passes, post success to channel with production screenshots. This is the 'careful merge' option — use !merge for quick merges, this for important releases.",
